description: This private apartment is centrally located in the heart of Portland.  We are walking distance to the Convention Center, Max line, and great bars and restaurants.  Downtown, Hawthorne, and Alberta neighborhoods are all only a 15 min bike ride away! I have taken great care finishing this space over the last 2 years.  While it is a basement it does not feel like one.  I put in one full size glass door and an oversized egress window to let in as much light as possible.  I sealed off all the vents and put in wall heaters to reduce noise between the spaces.  I also insulated the ceiling and walls with dense-packed fiberglass and hung noise-reducing RC channel beneath the ceiling sheetrock.  While you can tell there is someone upstairs if you listen close, it is much quieter than most apartments. You have your own entrance so if you want your privacy, no problem.  Our dog, Bo, will sometimes be across the gate in the back yard.  He is super friendly but might bark for a minute if surprised.
name: Portland's best kept secret...
